data.title: Marines TV
data.meta_description: U.S. Marine Lt. Col. Vanessa Clark takes command of Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 268 from outgoing commander U.S. Marine Lt. Col. Richard Alvarez during an airborne lead change at Marine Corps Base Hawaii, Dec. 4, 2020. With the traditional change of command ceremony canceled due to COVID-19 mitigation measures, the symbolic passing of the Colors was replaced by Lt. Col. Clark taking the flight lead from Lt. Col. Alvarez. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Jacob Wilson)
